 soon as tomorrow. Schedule your delivery in checkout. Save to List $8.28 ($2.76/item) Delivery Delivering to 10030 (1 item) Your Delivery Cost: FREE product 1 DRYLOK Extreme 1 gal. Bright White Flat Latex Interior/Exterior Basement and Masonry Waterproofer Model #831985 Cart Analysis: Let's Optimize This Right Now Looking at your actual cart, I see some smart choices and some unnecessary items that are costing you money. Let me break this down with brutal honesty. CURRENT CART TOTAL: ~$142.85 Let me analyze each item: ✅ KEEP - Essential Core Items ($86.34) Item\tQty\tPrice\tStatus\tNotes Sikaflex Self-Leveling 10.1 oz\t1\t$9.97\t✅ KEEP\tPerfect primary sealant SAKRETE Leak Stopper 20 lb\t1\t$26.97\t✅ KEEP\tInterior basement side DRYLOK Fast Plug 10 lb\t1\t$21.98\t✅ KEEP\tExterior foundation side SikaLatex Bonding Adhesive 1 Qt\t1\t$10.97\t✅ KEEP\tCritical for proper adhesion Fabral Butyl Tape 1/4\" x 40 ft\t1\t$5.98\t✅ KEEP\tExcellent backup barrier Master Flow Adjustable Elbow\t2\t$13.46\t✅ KEEP\tReplacement + spare Everbilt Snap-Lock Pipe 4\" x 2 ft\t4\t$21.92\t⚠️ REDUCE to 3\tYou only need 3 sections Subtotal for Essentials: $82.37 (after reducing pipes to 3) ❌ REMOVE - Unnecessary/Duplicate Items ($43.06 in savings) Item\tQty\tPrice\tWhy Remove\tImpact Frost King Caulk Saver (backer rod)\t1\t$1.48\t❌ NOT NEEDED for small dryer vent\tYour gap is small - hydraulic cement fills it completely Nashua Duct Tape\t1\t$6.48\t❌ CODE VIOLATION\tTape is NOT allowed for permanent duct connections per IRC M1502 Master Flow Splice Collar\t2\t$15.36\t❌ REDUNDANT\tYour snap-lock pipes connect directly - no collars needed Everbilt Worm Clamps 3\"-4\"\t3\t$8.28\t⚠️ KEEP ONLY 2\tNeed 2 for vent cap connections, 3rd is redundant DRYLOK Extreme 1 gal Paint\t1\t$11.46\t❌ WRONG PRODUCT\tThis is waterproof PAINT, not cement - you don't need interior painting Extra Snap-Lock Pipe\t1\t$5.48\t❌ REDUCE QTY\tYou have 4, only need 3 sections Total Removals/Reductions: Save $43.06 🚨 CRITICAL ISSUES IN YOUR CART ISSUE #1: Duct Tape is a Code Violation Nashua Duct Tape ($6.48) - ❌ REMOVE IMMEDIATELY Why This Is Dangerous: IRC M1502.4.2 states: \"Joints shall be made with metallic fasteners or clamps\" Duct tape deteriorates from dryer heat (130-160°F continuous) Creates lint buildup at seams (fire hazard) Adhesive breaks down in 6-24 months Insurance may deny claims if fire occurs and tape is found What You Should Use Instead: Your snap-lock pipes have crimped male/female ends - they snap together without tape For extra security at elbows: Use the worm clamps you already have (metallic, code-compliant) This is non-negotiable. Remove the tape from your cart. ISSUE #2: Splice Collars Are Redundant Master Flow Splice Collar x2 ($15.36) - ❌ REMOVE Why You Don't Need These: Your Everbilt snap-lock pipes have: Male crimped end (narrower) Female crimped end (wider) They connect directly to each other AND to the Master Flow elbows (which also have crimped ends). Splice collars are only needed when: Connecting two female ends together Connecting two male ends together Repairing damaged crimped ends You have none of these scenarios. The collars add zero functionality and cost you $15.36 for nothing. Save $15.36 - Remove these. ISSUE #3: DRYLOK Extreme is Paint, Not Cement DRYLOK Extreme 1 gal Waterproofer ($11.46) - ❌ REMOVE What This Actually Is: Waterproof masonry PAINT for coating basement walls Applied with brush/roller like regular paint For treating large wall surfaces (75-100 sq ft coverage) Why You Don't Need It: You already have DRYLOK Fast Plug cement ($21.98) - that's the structural repair product Your 4-layer system already waterproofs the penetration You're not painting your entire foundation wall This adds zero value to a 4\" duct penetration Possible Confusion: You may have thought this was another cement product because it says \"DRYLOK.\" But DRYLOK makes two different product lines: ✅ DRYLOK Fast Plug (hydraulic cement - you have this) ❌ DRYLOK Extreme (paint - remove this) Save $11.46 - Remove this. ISSUE #4: Backer Rod Is Unnecessary Frost King Caulk Saver 1/2\" ($1.48) - ❌ REMOVE When Backer Rod IS Needed: Large gaps (>1/2\" wide) Deep joints where sealant would waste product Expansion joints in driveways/sidewalks Your Situation: 4\" dryer duct through foundation Gap around duct is typically 1/4\" - 3/8\" (builder's standard) Hydraulic cement fills this completely in one application Backer rod would actually make your job HARDER: You'd have to stuff foam into irregular gap Then apply cement over it Cement bonds better to concrete than to foam Creates unnecessary interface/potential failure point Save $1.48 - Remove this. ISSUE #5: Too Many Worm Clamps Everbilt Worm Clamps 3\"-4\" (Qty: 3 = $8.28) - ⚠️ REDUCE to 2 Where Clamps ARE Needed: Securing final pipe section to exterior vent cap (if cap has smooth collar) Securing first pipe section to dryer connection (already at dryer) You Need: Maximum 2 clamps (one for each end connection) You Have: 3 clamps Remove 1 clamp - Save $2.76 New Clamp Total: 2 clamps = $5.52 ISSUE #6: One Extra Pipe Section Everbilt Snap-Lock Pipe (Qty: 4 = $21.92) - ⚠️ REDUCE to 3 You Stated Earlier: \"Replacing 3 rusted aluminum pipes\" You Have in Cart: 4 pipes Recommendation: ✅ Keep 3 pipes for the replacement sections ✅ You already have 2 elbows (one backup) ❌ Remove 4th pipe - unnecessary backup If you want a spare: Keep the 2nd elbow (already in cart) - elbows fail more often than straight sections Remove 1 pipe - Save $5.48 New Pipe Total: 3 pipes = $16.44 OPTIMIZED CART - FINAL RECOMMENDATION Item\tQty\tPrice\tPurpose\tAction Everbilt 4\" x 2 ft Snap-Lock Pipe\t3\t$16.44\tReplace 3 rusted sections\t✅ KEEP (reduce from 4) Master Flow 4\" Adjustable Elbow\t2\t$13.46\tReplace elbow + backup\t✅ KEEP SAKRETE Leak Stopper 20 lb\t1\t$26.97\tInterior basement side\t✅ KEEP DRYLOK Fast Plug 10 lb\t1\t$21.98\tExterior foundation side\t✅ KEEP SikaLatex Bonding Adhesive 1 Qt\t1\t$10.97\tChemical bond to concrete\t✅ KEEP Sikaflex Self-Leveling 10.1 oz\t1\t$9.97\tPrimary sealant\t✅ KEEP Fabral Butyl Tape 1/4\" x 40 ft\t1\t$5.98\tBackup barrier\t✅ KEEP Everbilt Worm Clamps 3\"-4\"\t2\t$5.52\tEnd connections\t✅ KEEP (reduce from 3) ❌ Nashua Duct Tape\t1\t$6.48\tCode violation\t❌ REMOVE ❌ Master Flow Splice Collar\t2\t$15.36\tRedundant\t❌ REMOVE ❌ DRYLOK Extreme P"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=37c050d9-748c-4b8c-829d-4c21f5f3ca5b","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=37c050d9-748c-4b8c-829d-4c21f5f3ca5b"}]}]}]
